Between their race cars and rapid-fire dialects, the Italians are known for
keeping a molto rapido pace. This recipe is an homage to that speed—it turns
traditional pasta amatriciana (pasta with pancetta) into a meal that can be
prepared in just 20 minutes. You'll be crushing the tomatoes for the sauce
with your hands, just to get a feel for that Old World rusticity. But once
they go in the pan, everything comes together with just a few easy stirs.

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil.

> TIP: Keep it covered to speed things up.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Trim woody bottom ends from
@asparagus{8%oz}, then cut stalks into 1-inch pieces.

Add onion and half the @pancetta{2%oz} to pan once hot (use remaining pancetta
as you like). Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}.
Cook, tossing, until onion is soft and pancetta is crisped, about ~{5%minutes}.
Meanwhile, place @whole peeled tomatoes{14%oz} in a #medium bowl and break up
with your hands into small pieces.

Once water is boiling, add @tagliatelle{6%oz} to #pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until chewy on the outside but still firm in the center,
~{6-7%minutes}. Add asparagus to #pot and cook until bright green and just
tender, ~{3-5%minutes} more (the tagliatelle should be al dente at this point).
Carefully scoop out and reserve 1 cup cooking water, then drain.

While tagliatelle cooks, add tomatoes and ½ cup water to pan with pancetta and
onion. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a gentle simmer. Season
with salt and pepper. Let simmer until tagliatelle and asparagus are ready.

After you've drained the tagliatelle and asparagus, reduce heat under pan with
sauce to low. Stir in @peas{4%oz} and @cream cheese{2%oz}. Cook, stirring,
until cream cheese is fully mixed in and peas are warmed through, about
~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add tagliatelle, asparagus, and ¼ cup reserved cooking water to pan with
sauce. Toss to combine and evenly coat. Season with salt and pepper. Add more
pasta water as needed if mixture seems dry. Divide between plates and sprinkle
with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}.